          • [ - ] mikka - member since 21-Sep-13

            0-4 for PSG. maybe even 5, Here is why: Zlatan scored 5 goals in his last three games (a double against Benfica, 1 against Marseille, another brace versus Bastia + 1 goal with his national team) Cavani score one goal on his last game with Uruguay against Argentina & he also scored a brace against Bastia which gives him a total of 3 goals in his last two games and 7 in 8 games overall. Also Lavezzi scored a double in his last game, with Argentina so it's 10 goals scored between the 3 of them in their last 3 matches, that's what i call being in form. PSG played 12 games so far winning 9 times (2 in the CL) & drawing 3. Scoring 25 goals (7 in CL) & conceding only 6 goals (1 in CL) along the way. They average 66.7% possession in cl (third only after Bayern and Barca) & 90.9% pass accuracy, the best in the competition & the only team above 90%. Finally they boost the best goal conversion rate of the tournament, 21 shots, 15 on target, 7 goals = 33.3%.
